BANKROLL broke sharp and took back off the pace, raced six wide down the backside, was asked to start running at the half mile pole, responded well and went into the second turn five wide, circled the field, was the first one to the quarter pole, showed the way from there until the last sixteenth of a mile where he was run down late by an unexpected foe and had to settle for second. CHROMPTON was bumped at the start, regained his balance and settled mid pack five wide down the backside, was encouraged to make up ground at the half mile pole, responded well and chased through the turn, was two wide at the upper stretch, closed gamely but had to much to do, was able to pick up third place honors. J B GRAY broke very hard into the two horse, was corrected, stalked the leader, was well placed and in contention through the turn, was pushed out leaving the turn by an inside, foe, was six wide in the stretch, was encouraged and kept on point but didn't have enough today. THE THREE KS vied for the early lead, matched strides for two furlongs with another rival, took command and showed the way, was collared at the quarter pole, and flattened out late. ONE TOUGH CHARLIE vied for the early lead, battled for two furlongs, took back and stalked from the two path, stopped after the quarter pole. CPRIORITY was off slow, raced four wide, was eased in the stretch.
